{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784056143,"nonce":"ZkfmwYfsvG8BtLOxB6yZFfcx2uc=","message":"Fixed and MERGED as PR #105 (squash `4b07991`).\n\nPostgreSQL has only `smallint`/`integer`/`bigint`/`numeric` for integers, so the twelve neutral integer widths render lossily to those four. A faithful inverse is impossible, so each width now canonicalizes (in the diff only) to the signed representative its rendered type introspects back to — the same fold `canonical_pg_pin_type` already applied to a view result pin, now shared:\n\n- `canonical_pg_sql_type`: `I8/U8 → I16`, `U16 → I32`, `Isize/U32/Usize → I64`, `I128/U64/U128 → I128`, on both sides. Also folds an explicit `#[column(db_type = \"numeric\")]` (`Raw(\"numeric\")`/`Raw(\"decimal\")`, case-insensitively) to `I128`, so all four spellings that render to bare `numeric` converge.\n- `canonical_pg_default`: reconciles integer defaults to `Int` — a desired unsigned literal (`UInt`) and an introspected bare-`numeric` `Raw(\"9\")` both fold, so an unsigned/wide column with a default also re-plans empty.\n\nIntrospection stays faithful — bare `numeric` reads back as `Raw(\"numeric\")`, NOT `I128`, so `squealy extract` of a genuine arbitrary-precision numeric column is not misrepresented. All reconciliation lives in `canonicalize_model`, which the extract path does not run.\n\nDesign (both maintainer-confirmed): (1) Option A — canonicalize, lossy-but-consistent (a `U8` column is planned as `smallint`); (2) keep introspection accurate + reconcile in the diff only.\n\nLocal codex 3 rounds: R1 (P1) my initial `numeric → I128` introspection conflated an explicit `Raw(\"numeric\")` column → churn; R2 (P2) match `numeric`/`decimal` case-insensitively (`parse_db_type` preserves user casing in the `Raw` fallback); R3 (P2) `numeric → I128` introspection corrupted the `extract`/export path → reverted to accurate introspection, moved all reconciliation into canonicalization. Then clean.\n\nAccepted residual: a `U128` default above `i128::MAX` has no `Int` representation and reads back as `Raw`; documented on `canonical_pg_default`.\n\nPG-scoped (MySQL/SQLite untouched). Verified: fmt, workspace clippy `-D warnings`, full `--all-features` workspace test, compile_fail; live `#[ignore]` on fresh PG — new round-trip fixture (every collapsed width + two defaults + an explicit `db_type = \"numeric\"` column) re-plans empty; `squealy-model`/`squealy-postgresql` publish+integration live suites pass.","files":null}]}